commitResults.messageTitle: Add chat bot class, list things to do
Add Task class, mark as done
Delete tasks, change mark done a bit
Add feature "Save data to hard disk, load data from hard disk"
commitResults.messageBody:
Add a "FileHandler" class with two functions (read and update).

The file will be updated only when the program terminates instead
of appending tasks to the file when user is using. It might
not be that efficient, but the number of tasks from the user
will not be very large, hence the performance will be okay.

However, the file path specified is not an OS-independent way.
Hence, changes need to be made to let Duke be OS-independent.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change Deadline and Event String time into LocalDate time
commitResults.messageBody:
Restrict user input of time element (event, deadline) to format (yyyy-mm-dd).
Format the output of time to (mmm dd yyyy). Handle DateTimeParseException
causing by this new feature.
This changing is made to clearly distinguish TODO event and todo list.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add class Ui, Parser, Command, TaskList
commitResults.messageBody:
- Ui: deals with interactions with the user
- Parser: deals with making sense of the user command
- TaskList: contains the task list
- Command: use enum deal with different commands

commitResults.messageTitle: Package all the classes other than Duke in a package
commitResults.messageBody:
Since the dependencies of the classes are a bit messy,
all classes other than Duke are package in the same
package for now.

Looking forward to making the dependencies clearer,
and thus have nicer packaging.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change package name, JUnit test, Create JAR file
commitResults.messageBody:
Packages are mostly named in lower case, so the package
is renamed to lower case. By doing JUnit test, some exception
handlings are added in class TaskList. Create the JAR file,
and published on github as Duke v0.1.

commitResults.messageTitle: Connect the chatbot to the GUI
commitResults.messageBody:
Handle the user input, and give the corresponding duke reply.
Create two new packages: duke.gui, duke.task. Because of the
packaging, the constructor of each subclass of tasks should become
public. Move most of the things into ChatBot class, and Duke class
become a class only be used for CLI.

Modify the return values of functions in TaskList class from void to String,
so that it can be used in handleUserInput function in MainWindow class.
However, the JavaDoc remains the same for now. Hence, a lot of
JavaDoc needs to be changed.

Change the background color of MainWindow and Dialog box.
Fix import problems and check naming conventions.

The JavaDoc hasn't been changed yet.
